 they explore three dimensions of democracy promotion: elections, free media, and human rights. Drawing on the experiences of Afghanistan, Cambodia, El Salvador, Ethiopia, Guatemala, Mozambique, Rwanda, Sierra Leone, and Uganda, they suggest concrete ways in which the international community can better foster democratization in the wake of conflict.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Peace.2bisacsh1 aAyenew, Meheret, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAzpuru, Dinorah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarya, John-Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoor, Luc van de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHughes, Charlie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKayumba, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKimonyo, Jean-Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKumar, Krishna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKumar, Krishna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLefèvre, Anne Germain, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNzongola-Ntalaja, Georges, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeou, Sorpong, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRahmato, Dessalegn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSesay, Mohamed Gibril, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTollenaere, Marc de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWierda, Marieke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZeeuw, Jeroen de, econtributor.4ctb